obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (23204)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23204&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Institutes of Information`
  line `Technology Act, 2014.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 5th January, 2015, vide notification No. S.O. 41(E) , dated 5th January, 2015, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (23205)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration of certain institutions as institutions of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23205&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Whereas the objects`
  line `of the Institutes mentioned in the Schedule are such as to make them institutions of national importance, it`
  line `is hereby declared that each such Institute is an institution of national importance.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (23206)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23206&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Board", in relation to any Institute, means the Board of Governors referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Board of Governors appointed under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(c) "Council" means the Council established under sub-section (1) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(d) "Director" means the Director of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(e) "existing Institute" means the institute mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(f) "Institute" means any of the institutions mentioned in column (5) of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "Schedule" means the Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "Senate", in relation to any Institute, means the Senate thereof;`
  line
  line `(j) "Statutes" and "Ordinances", in relation to any Institute, means the Statutes and Ordinances of`
  line `the Institute made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (23207)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Incorporation of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23207&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the commencement of this Act, every existing`
  line `Institute, shall be a body corporate by the same name as mentioned in column (5) of the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Every existing Institute referred to in column (5) of the Schedule shall have perpetual succession`
  line `and a common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property, both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (23208)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Effect of incorporation of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23208&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the commencement of this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to a Society in any contract or other instrument shall be deemed as a reference`
  line `to the corresponding Institute mentioned in column (5) of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) all properties, movable and immovable, of or belonging to every existing Institute shall vest in`
  line `the corresponding Institute mentioned under column (5) of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(c) all rights and debts and other liabilities of every existing Institute mentioned in column (3) of`
  line `the Schedule shall be transferred to, and be the rights and liabilities of, the corresponding Institute`
  line `mentioned in column (5) of the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(d) every person employed by every existing Institute mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule,`
  line `immediately before such commencement shall hold his office or service in the corresponding Institute`
  line `mentioned in column (5) of the Schedule, with the same tenure, at the same remuneration and upon`
  line `the same terms and conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to pension, leave, gratuity,`
  line `provident fund and other matters as he would have held the same if this Act had not been enacted and`
  line `shall continue to do so unless and until his employment is terminated or until such tenure,`
  line `remuneration and terms and conditions are duly altered by the Statutes:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the alteration so made is not acceptable to such employee, his employment may`
  line `be terminated by the Institute in accordance with the terms of the contract with the employee or, if no`
  line `provision is made therein in this behalf, on payment, to him by the Institute, of compensation`
  line `equivalent to three months' remuneration in case of permanent employees and one month's`
  line `remuneration in the case of other employees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any reference, by whatever form of words, to the Director, Registrar and`
  line `other officers of an existing Institute mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule, in any law for the time`
  line `being in force, or in any instrument or other document, shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `Director, Registrar and other officers of the corresponding Institute mentioned in column (5) of the`
  line Schedule;
  line
  line `(e) every person pursuing, before the commencement of this Act, any academic or research`
  line `course in every existing Institute mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule, shall be deemed to have`
  line `migrated and registered with the corresponding Institute mentioned in column (5) of the Schedule, on`
  line `such commencement at the same level of course in the Institute from which such person migrated;`
  line
  line `(f) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or`
  line `against an existing Institute, mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule, immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall be continued or instituted by or against the corresponding Institute`
  line `mentioned in column (5) of the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (23209)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Objects of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23209&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Each Institute shall have the following objects, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to emerge amongst the foremost institutions in information technology and allied fields of`
  line knowledge;
  line
  line `(b) to advance new knowledge and innovation in information technology and allied fields to`
  line `empower the nation to the forefront in the global context;`
  line
  line `(c) to develop competent and capable youth imbued with the spirit of innovation and`
  line `entrepreneurship with the social and environmental orientation to meet the knowledge needs of the`
  line `country and provide global leadership in information technology and allied fields;`
  line
  line `(d) to promote and provide transparency of highest order in matters of admission, appointments`
  line `to various positions, academic evaluation, administration and finance.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (23210)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Powers and functions of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23210&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, every Institute shall`
  line `exercise the following powers and perform the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to provide instruction in such fields of knowledge concerning information technology and`
  line `allied areas as such Institute may think fit, for the advancement of learning and dissemination of`
  line knowledge;
  line
  line `(b) to lead, organise and conduct research and innovation in information technology and allied`
  line `fields of knowledge in such manner as the Institute may think fit, including in collaboration or in`
  line `association with any other Institute, educational institution, research organisation or body corporate;`
  line
  line `(c) to hold examinations and grant degrees, diplomas and other academic distinctions or titles;`
  line `and to confer honorary degrees;`
  line
  line `(d) to institute teaching, research or other academic positions, required by the Institute with such`
  line `designations as it may deem fit, and to appoint persons on tenure, term or otherwise to such positions,`
  line `other than the post of Director in accordance with the policy laid down by the Council;`
  line
  line `(e) to appoint persons working in any other Institute or educational institution or involved in`
  line `research of significance in any industry as adjunct, guest or visiting faculty of the Institute on such`
  line `terms and for such duration as the Institute may decide;`
  line
  line `(f) to create administrative and other posts and to make appointments thereto in accordance with`
  line `the policy laid down by the Council;`
  line
  line `(g) to make provision for dissemination of knowledge emerging from research and for that`
  line `purpose to enter into such arrangements, including consultancy and advisory services, with other`
  line `institutions, industry, civil society or other organisations, as the Institute may deem necessary;`
  line
  line `(h) to create a website, highlight all information not restricted to those related to students,`
  line `admission, fee, administrative structure, policies including recruitment rules, faculty and non-faculty`
  line `posts, annual reports and financial details including statement of account of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(i) to determine, specify and receive payment of the charges, as the Institute may deem fit, from`
  line `person, institution or body corporate for services, including training, consultancy and advisory`
  line `services, provided by the Institute;`
  line
  line `(j) to deal with any property belonging to or vested in, the Institute in such manner as the Institute`
  line `may deem fit for advancing the objects of the Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the land for the Institute has been provided free of cost by a State`
  line `Government, such land may be disposed of only with the prior approval of such State Government;`
  line
  line `(k) to receive gifts, grants, donations or benefactions from the Government and to receive`
  line `bequests, donations and transfers of movable or immovable properties from testators, donors or`
  line `transferors, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(l) to co-operate with educational or other institutions in any part of the world having objects`
  line `wholly or partly similar to those of the Institute by exchange of teachers and scholars and generally in`
  line `such manner as may be conducive to their common objects;`
  line
  line `(m) to establish and maintain such infrastructure as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to`
  line `the attainment of the objects of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(n) to institute and award fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, prizes and medals;`
  line
  line `(o) to strive to meet the technological needs of the States and the Union territories by supporting`
  line `technical educational institutions; and`
  line
  line `(p) to do all such things as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the attainment of all or`
  line `any of the objects of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (j), an Institute shall not dispose of in any manner`
  line `any immovable property, without the prior approval of the Visitor.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (23211)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Institute to be open to all races, creeds and classes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23211&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute shall be open to all`
  line `persons irrespective of gender, caste, creed, disability, domicile, ethnicity, social or economic`
  line background.
  line
  line `(2) No bequest, donation or transfer of any property shall be accepted by any Institute which in the`
  line `opinion of the Council involves conditions or obligations opposed to the spirit and object of this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Admissions to every programme of study in each Institute shall be based on merit assessed`
  line `through transparent and reasonable criteria disclosed through its prospectus, prior to the commencement`
  line `of the process of admission by such Institute:`
  line
  line `Provided that every such Institute shall be a Central Educational Institution for the purposes of the`
  line `Central Educational Institutions (Reservation in Admission) Act, 2006 (5 of 2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (23212)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Teaching at Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23212&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All teaching at each of the Institute shall be conducted by or in the name`
  line `of the Institute in accordance with the Statutes and Ordinances made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (23213)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Institute to be a distinct legal entity not-for-profit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23213&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Each Institute shall be a not-for-profit`
  line `legal entity and no part of the surplus, if any, in revenue of such Institute, after meeting all expenditure in`
  line `regard to its operations under this Act, shall be invested for any purpose other than for the growth and`
  line `development of such Institute or for conducting research therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (23214)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Visitor.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23214&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of India shall be the Visitor of every Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Visitor may appoint one or more persons to review the work and progress of any Institute and`
  line `to hold inquiries into the affairs thereof and to report thereon in such manner as the Visitor may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon receipt of any such report, the Visitor may take such action and issue such directions as he`
  line `considers necessary in respect of any of the matters dealt with in the report and the Institute shall be`
  line `bound to comply with such directions within a reasonable time.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (23215)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Authorities of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23215&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be the authorities of an Institute, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) Board of Governors;`
  line
  line `(b) Senate;`
  line
  line `(c) Finance Committee;`
  line
  line `(d) Building and Works Committee;`
  line
  line `(e) Research Council;`
  line
  line `(f) such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (23216)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Board of Governors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23216&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Governors of each Institute shall be the principal`
  line `executive body of that Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board of Governors of each Institute shall consist of the following members, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, an eminent technologist or industrialist or educationist to be nominated by the`
  line `Visitor from a panel of three names recommended by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) Secretary incharge of Information Technology or Higher Education in the State in which the`
  line `Institute is located, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) one representative of the Department of Higher Education, Government of India dealing with`
  line `Indian Institute of Information Technology, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) one representative of the Ministry of Communication and Information Technology,`
  line `Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) Director of Indian Institute of Technology to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) Director of Indian Institute of Management to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(g) four persons having special knowledge or practical experience in respect of information`
  line `technology or engineering or science or allied areas to be nominated by the Council;`
  line
  line `(h) two Professors of the Institute nominated by the Senate;`
  line
  line `(i) Director of the Institute, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(j) the Registrar, ex officio Secretary.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (23217)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Term of office of, vacancies among, and allowances payable to, members of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23217&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this section, the term of office of member of the Board, other than the`
  line `ex officio member, shall be three years from the date of nomination.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as he holds the office by virtue`
  line `of which he is a member.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of a member nominated under clause (h) of sub-section (2) of section 13 shall`
  line `be two years from the date of nomination.`
  line
  line `(4) A member of the Board, other than an ex officio member, who fails to attend three consecutive`
  line `meetings of the Board, shall cease to a member of the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, an outgoing member shall, unless the Council`
  line `directs, continue in office until another person is nominated as a member in his place.`
  line
  line `(6) Members of the Board shall be entitled to such allowances, as may be specified in the Statutes, for`
  line `attending meetings of the Board or as may be convened by the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (23218)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Powers and functions of Board of Governors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23218&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `Board of every Institute shall be responsible for the general superintendence, direction and control of the`
  line `affairs of the Institute and shall have the power to frame, amend, modify or rescind the Statutes and`
  line `Ordinances governing the affairs of the Institute to achieve the objects specified in section 6.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board shall have the following powers,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to take decisions on questions of policy relating to the administration and working of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(b) to establish departments, faculties or schools of studies and initiate programmes or courses of`
  line `study at the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) to examine and approve the annual budget estimates of such Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) to examine and approve the plan for development of such Institute and to identify sources of`
  line `finance for implementation of the plan;`
  line
  line `(e) to create teaching and other academic posts, to determine, by Statutes, the number and`
  line `emoluments of such posts and to define the duties and conditions of service of teachers and other`
  line `academic staff:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall not take action otherwise than on consideration of the`
  line `recommendations of the Senate;`
  line
  line `(f) to provide, by Statutes, the qualifications, criteria and processes for appointment to teaching`
  line `and other posts in such Institute;`
  line
  line `(g) to fix fees, by the Statutes and other charges to be demanded for pursuit of studies in the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(h) to make Statutes governing the administration, management and operations of such Institute;`
  line and
  line
  line `(i) to exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed`
  line `upon it by this Act or Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have the power to appoint such committees, as it considers necessary for the`
  line `exercise of its powers and the performance of its duties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall conduct an annual review of the performance of the Direct with specific`
  line `reference to his leadership in the context of the achievement of the objects of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(5) Where in the opinion of the Director or the Chairperson, the situation is so emergent that an`
  line `immediate decision needs to be taken in the interest of the Institute, the Chairperson, in consultation with`
  line `the Director may issue such orders as may be necessary, recording the grounds for his opinion:`
  line
  line `Provided that such orders shall be submitted for ratification of the Board in the next meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (23219)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Senate.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23219&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Senate of each Institute shall consist of the following persons, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) Director of the Institute, ex officio Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) Deputy Director, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Deans, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) Heads of the Departments of the Institute, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) all Professors other than the Deans or Heads of the Departments;`
  line
  line `(f) three persons from amongst educationists of repute or persons from another field related to the`
  line `activities of the Institute who are not in service of the Institute, nominated by the Board of Governors;`
  line
  line `(g) three persons who are not members of teaching staff co-opted by the Senate for their`
  line `specialised knowledge;`
  line
  line `(h) Registrar of the Institute, ex officio Secretary.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of members other than ex officio member shall be two years from the date of`
  line nomination.
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as he holds the office by virtue`
  line `of which he is a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (23220)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Powers and functions of Senate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23220&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Senate shall be`
  line `the principal academic body of the Institute and shall have the power to enact, amend, modify`
  line `Ordinances, governing academic matters and the affairs and well-being of students in the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Senate shall have the following powers,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to specify the criteria and process for admission to courses or programmes of study offered by`
  line `the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) to recommend to the Board creation of teaching and other academic posts, determination of`
  line `the number and emoluments of such posts and defining the duties and conditions of service of`
  line `teachers and other academic posts;`
  line
  line `(c) to recommend to the Board about commencement of new programmes or courses of study;`
  line
  line `(d) to specify the broad academic content of programmes and courses of study and undertake`
  line `modifications therein;`
  line
  line `(e) to specify the academic calendar and approve grant of degrees, diplomas and other academic`
  line `distinctions or titles;`
  line
  line `(f) to appoint examiners, moderators, tabulators and such other personnel for different`
  line examinations;
  line
  line `(g) to recognise diplomas and degrees or Universities and other Institutes and to determine`
  line `equivalence with the diplomas and degrees of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(h) to suggest measures for departmental co-ordination;`
  line
  line `(i) to make major recommendations to the Board of Governors on—`
  line
  line `(a) measures for improvement of standard of teaching, training and research;`
  line
  line `(b) institution of chairs, fellowships, scholarships, studentships, free-ships, medals and prizes`
  line `and other related matters;`
  line
  line `(c) establishment or abolition of departments or centres; and`
  line
  line `(d) bye-laws covering the academic functioning of the institute, discipline, residence,`
  line `admissions, examinations, award of fellowships and studentships, free-ships concessions,`
  line `attendance and other related matters;`
  line
  line `(j) to appoint sub-committees to advise on such specific matters as may be referred to by the`
  line `Board of Governors or by itself;`
  line
  line `(k) to consider the recommendations of the sub-committees and to take such action including`
  line `making of recommendations to the Board of Governors as may be required;`
  line
  line `(l) to take periodical review of the activities of the Departments or Centres and to take appropriate`
  line `action including making of recommendations to the Board of Governors with a view to maintain and`
  line `improve the standards of instructions, in the institutions; and`
  line
  line `(m) to exercise such other powers and discharge such other functions as may be assigned to it, by`
  line `Statutes or otherwise, by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (23221)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Finance Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23221&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Finance Committee of each Institute shall consist of the following`
  line `persons, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson, Board of Governors, ex officio, who shall be the Chairperson of the`
  line Committee;
  line
  line `(b) one representative of the Government of India, Ministry of Human Resource Development,`
  line `Department of Higher Education handling the matters relating to Indian Institute of Information`
  line `Technology, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) one representative of the Government of India, Ministry of Human Resource Development,`
  line `Department of Higher Education handling the matters relating to finance, ex officio;`
  line `(d) two persons nominated by the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) the Director, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Officer incharge of Finance and Accounts of the Institute, ex officio Secretary.`
  line
  line `(2) The members of the Finance Committee other than ex officio members shall hold office for a term`
  line `of three years.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (23222)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power and functions of Finance Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23222&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Finance Committee shall examine the`
  line `accounts, scrutinise proposals for expenditure and financial estimates of the Institute and thereafter submit`
  line `it to the Board of Governors together with its comments for approval.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (23223)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Building and Works Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23223&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Building and Works Committee of each Institute shall`
  line `consist of the following persons, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the Director, ex officio, who shall be the Chairperson of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) one person nominated by Indian Institute of Technology located in the State in which the`
  line `Institute is situated;`
  line
  line `(c) one person nominated by the Board from amongst its members;`
  line
  line `(d) Dean, Planning and Development;`
  line
  line `(e) a civil engineer not below the rank of superintending engineer in the Government or`
  line `Government Agency nominated by the Board;`
  line
  line `(f) an electrical engineer not below the rank of superintending engineer in the Government or`
  line `Government Agency nominated by the Board;`
  line
  line `(g) the officer incharge of Estate of the Institute, ex officio Secretary.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (23224)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Powers and functions of Building and Works Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23224&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Building and Works`
  line `Committee shall discharge the following powers and functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) it shall be the responsibility of the Committee for construction of all major capital works after`
  line `securing from the Board the necessary administrative approval and financial sanction;`
  line
  line `(b) it shall have the power to give the necessary administrative approval and financial sanction for`
  line `all construction work and work pertaining to maintenance and repairs, within the grant place at the`
  line `disposal of the Institute for the purpose;`
  line
  line `(c) it shall cause to be prepared estimates of cost of building and other capital work, minor works,`
  line `repair, maintenance and the like;`
  line
  line `(d) it shall be responsible for making technical scrutiny of each work as may be considered`
  line `necessary by it;`
  line
  line `(e) it shall be responsible for enlistment of suitable contractors and acceptance of tenders and`
  line `shall have the power to give direction for departmental works where necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (23225)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Research Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23225&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Institute shall establish a Research Council comprising of the`
  line `Director and such other members as may be specified, by Statutes, by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Research Council of each Institute shall—`
  line
  line `(a) interface with research funding organisations, industry and civil society to identify potential`
  line `areas for research;`
  line
  line `(b) to organise and promote research in such Institute or in collaboration with any institution of`
  line `higher learning or research laboratories;`
  line
  line `(c) assist teachers in obtaining funding from external sources for research projects prepared by`
  line them;
  line
  line `(d) provide, out of the funds placed at its disposal by the Board, research resources and grant`
  line `assistance for research projects proposed to be undertaken by teachers in such Institute;`
  line
  line `(e) provide for incubation of technology applications emerging from research and to protect and`
  line `utilise the intellectual property obtained from research in the Institutes;`
  line
  line `(f) make provision for research and advisory services and for that purpose enter into such`
  line `arrangements with other institutions, industry, civil society or other organisations and enable the fruits`
  line `of research to be disseminated to industry and society through such arrangements;`
  line
  line `(g) exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be assigned to it by Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (23226)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23226&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall ordinarily preside over the meetings of the Board, Finance`
  line `Committee and at the convocations of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Chairperson to ensure that the decisions taken by the Board are`
  line implemented.
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be`
  line `assigned to him by this Act or the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (23227)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Director.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2017, s. 2, for "Indian Institutes of Information Technology" (w.e.f. 7-9-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23227&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director of a Institute shall be appointed by the Central Government from a`
  line `panel of names recommended in order of merit by a search-cum-selection committee with prior approval`
  line `of the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(2) The search-cum-selection committee shall consist of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) an eminent person to be nominated by the Minister in charge of Human Resource`
  line `Development in the Government of India as Chairperson of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chairperson, Board of Governors of the concerned Indian Institutes of Information`
  line `Technology — Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Secretary incharge of Higher Education in the Government of India Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) Director of a ^1[Indian Institutes of Information Technology] to be nominated by Minister incharge of Human Resource Development — Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) a person of eminence in the field of information technology to be nominated by Minister`
  line `incharge of Human Resource Development;`
  line
  line `(f) Head of Bureau, Ministry of Human Resource Development dealing with Indian Institutes of`
  line `Information Technology — non-member Secretary, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director shall be appointed on such terms and conditions of service as may be provided by`
  line `the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director shall be the principal academic and executive officer of the Institute and shall be`
  line `responsible for the implementation of the decisions of the Board and Senate and day-to-day`
  line `administration of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(5) The Director shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be assigned to`
  line `him by this Act or the Statutes or delegated by the Board or the Senate or the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(6) The Director shall submit annual reports and audited accounts to the Board.`
  line
  line `(7) The Director may during his absence from the headquarters, authorise the Deputy Director or one`
  line `of the Deans or the senior most Professor present, to sanction advances for travelling allowances,`
  line `contingencies and medical treatment of the staff and sign and countersign bills on his behalf and authorise`
  line `to the Deputy Director or one of the Dean or the senior most Professor present, by him in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (23228)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title Registrar.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23228&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar of every Institute shall be appointed on such terms and conditions`
  line `as may be laid down by the Statutes and shall be the custodian of records, the common seal, the funds of`
  line `the Institute and such other property of the Institute as the Board shall commit to his charge.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall act as the Secretary of the Board, Senate and such committees as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall be responsible to the Director for the proper discharge of his functions.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be assigned`
  line `to him by this Act or the Statutes or by the Director.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (23229)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Other authorities and officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23229&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, by Statutes, declare such other posts as`
  line `authorities of the Institute and specify the duties and function of each such authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may constitute such authorities as it may deem fit for proper management of affairs of`
  line `the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (23230)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Review of performance of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23230&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each Institute shall, within five years from the`
  line `establishment and incorporation of Institute under this Act and thereafter at the expiration of every fifth`
  line `year, constitute, with the prior approval of the Central Government, a Committee to evaluate and review`
  line `the performance of the Institute in achievement of its objects in the said period.`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee under sub-section (1) shall consist of members of acknowledged repute in`
  line `academia or industry, drawn from such fields of knowledge as may have relevance to teaching, learning`
  line `and research in such Institute.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall assess the performance of Institute and make recommendations on—`
  line
  line `(a) the extent of fulfilment of the objects of the Institute referred to in section 6, as demonstrated`
  line `by the state of teaching, learning and research and its contribution to society;`
  line
  line `(b) the promotion of transformational research and its impact on industry and society;`
  line
  line `(c) the advancement of fundamental research beyond the current frontiers of knowledge;`
  line
  line `(d) the establishment of the Institute as amongst the global leaders in the area of information`
  line technology;
  line
  line `(e) such other matters as the Board may specify.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall consider the recommendations referred to in sub-section (3) and take such action`
  line `on it as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the recommendations of the Committee along with an explanatory memorandum on the`
  line `action taken or proposed to be taken, specifying the reasons thereof, shall be submitted to the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (23231)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23231&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of enabling the Institutes to discharge`
  line `their functions efficiently under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to each Institute in every financial year such sums of money in such`
  line `manner as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall provide to each Institute, grants of such sums of money as are`
  line `required to meet the expenditure on scholarships or fellowships instituted by it, including scholarships or`
  line `fellowships for students from socially and educationally backward classes of citizens enrolled in such`
  line Institute.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (23232)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Fund of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23232&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute shall maintain a fund to which shall be credited:—`
  line
  line `(a) all monies provided by the Central Government or State Government, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and other charges received by the Institute from students;`
  line
  line `(c) all monies received by the Institute by way of grants, gifts, donations, benefactions, bequests`
  line `or transfers;`
  line
  line `(d) all monies received by the Institute from utilisation of intellectual property arising from`
  line `research conducted or provision of advisory or consultancy services by it; and`
  line
  line `(e) all monies received by the Institute in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) The fund of every Institute shall be applied towards meeting the expenses of the Institute,`
  line `including expenses incurred in the exercise of its powers and discharge of its duties under this Act,`
  line `furtherance of research in the Institute or in collaboration with other educational institutions or industry`
  line `and for capital investment aimed at the growth and development of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (23233)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23233&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare annual statement of accounts including the balance sheet in such form and accounting`
  line `standard as may be specified by notification, by the Central Government in consultation with the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the statement of income and expenditure and the balance sheet of the Institute do not`
  line `comply with the accounting standards, the Institute shall disclose in its statement of income and`
  line `expenditure and balance sheet, the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the deviation from the accounting standards;`
  line
  line `(b) the reasons for such deviation; and`
  line
  line `(c) the financial effect, if any, arising out due to such deviation.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of every Institute shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `and any expenditure incurred by audit team in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Institute`
  line `to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(4) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of any Institute shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the rights to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the offices of the`
  line Institute.
  line
  line `(5) The accounts of every Institute as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament in accordance with such procedure as may be laid down by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (23234)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Pension and provident fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23234&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Institute may constitute for the benefit of its employees`
  line `such provident or pension fund or provide such insurance scheme as it may deem fit in such manner and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such provident fund or pension fund has been so constituted, the Central Government may`
  line `declare that the provisions of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925), shall apply to such fund, as if it`
  line `were a Government Provident Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (23235)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Appointments.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2017, s. 3, "Assistant Professor" (w.e.f. 7-9-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23235&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `All appointments of the staff of every Institute, except that of the Director, shall`
  line `be made in accordance with the procedure laid down in the Statutes, by—`
  line
  line `(a) the Board, if the appointment is made on the academic staff in the post of ^1`
  line [Assistant
  line `Professor or above] or if the appointment is made on the non-academic staff in every cadre the`
  line `maximum of the pay scale for which exceeds prevalent grade pay scale for Group A Officers;`
  line
  line `(b) the Director, in any other case`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (23236)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23236&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the conferment of honorary degree;`
  line
  line `(b) the formation of departments of teaching;`
  line
  line `(c) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the Institute and for admission to the`
  line `examinations of degrees and diplomas of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(e) the terms of office and the method of appointment of officers of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(f) the qualifications of teachers of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(g) the classification, the method of appointment and the determination of the terms and`
  line `conditions of service of teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(h) the constitution of pension, insurance and provident funds for the benefit of the officers,`
  line `teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(i) the constitution, powers and duties of the authorities of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(j) the establishment and maintenance of halls and hostels;`
  line
  line `(k) the conditions of residence of students of the Institute and the levying of fees for residence in`
  line `the halls and hostels and of other charges;`
  line
  line `(l) the allowances to be paid to the Chairperson and members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(m) the authentication of the orders and decisions of the Board; and`
  line
  line `(n) the meetings of the Board, the Senate, or any Committee, the quorum at such meetings and the`
  line `procedure to be followed in the conduct of their business.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (23237)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Statutes how to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23237&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The first Statutes of each Institute shall be made by the Board`
  line `with the prior approval of the Visitor and a copy of the same shall be laid as soon as may be before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, from time to time, make new or additional Statutes or may amend or repeal the`
  line `Statutes in the manner provided in this section.`
  line
  line `(3) Every new Statutes or addition to the Statutes or any amendment or repeal of Statutes shall require`
  line `the prior approval of the Visitor who may grant assent or withhold assent or remit it to the Board for`
  line consideration.
  line
  line `(4) New Statutes or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall have no validity unless it`
  line `has been assented to by the Visitor:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government with the prior approval of the Visitor may make or amend the`
  line `Statutes for the Institute, if the same is required for uniformity, and a copy of the same shall be laid as`
  line `soon as may be before each House of the Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (23238)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23238&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances of every`
  line `Institute may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of the students to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees and diplomas of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions under which students shall be admitted to the degree or diploma courses and to`
  line `the examinations of the Institute, and shall be eligible for degrees and diplomas;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions of award of the fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions and mode of appointment and duties of examining bodies, examiners and`
  line moderators;
  line
  line `(f) the conduct of examinations;`
  line
  line `(g) the maintenance of discipline among the students of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which by this Act or the Statutes is to be or may be provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (23239)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Ordinances how to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23239&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, Ordinances shall`
  line `be made by the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) All Ordinances made by the Senate shall have effect from such date as it may direct, but every`
  line `Ordinance so made shall be submitted, as soon as may be, to the Board and shall be considered by the`
  line `Board at its next meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have power by resolution to modify or cancel any such Ordinance and such`
  line `Ordinance shall from the date of such resolution stand modified accordingly or cancelled, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (23240)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23240&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) Any dispute arising out of a contract between a Institute and`
  line `any of its employees shall, at the request of the employee concerned or at the instance of the Institute, be`
  line `referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Institute, one member`
  line `nominated by the employee, and an umpire appointed by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(b) The decision of the Tribunal shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
  line
  line `(c) No suit or proceeding shall lie in any court in respect of any matter, which is required by`
  line `sub-section (1) to be referred to the Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  line
  line `(d) The Tribunal of Arbitration shall have power to regulate its own procedure:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal shall have regard to the principles of natural justice while making such`
  line procedure.
  line
  line `(e) Nothing in any law for the time being in force relating to arbitration shall apply to arbitrations`
  line `under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Any student or candidate for an examination whose name has been removed from the rolls of the`
  line `Institute by the orders or resolution of the Director of the Institute and who has been debarred from the`
  line `appearing at the examinations of the Institute for more than one year, may within ten days of the date of receipt of such resolution by him, appeal to the Board of Governors who may confirm, modify or reverse`
  line `the decision of the Director.`
  line
  line `(3) Any dispute arising out of any disciplinary action taken by the Institute against a student shall, at`
  line `the request of such student, be referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration and the provisions of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall, as far as may be, apply to a reference made under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) Every employee or student of the Institute, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, have a`
  line `right to appeal within such time as may be prescribed by the Statutes, to the Board of Governors against`
  line `the decision of any officer or authority of the Institute as the case may be and thereupon the Board of`
  line `Governors may confirm, modify or reverse the decision appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (23241)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Annual report of Director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23241&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be attached to every statement of accounts laid`
  line `before the Board of each Institute, a report by its Director, with respect to—`
  line
  line `(a) the state of affairs of such Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the amounts, if any, which it proposes to carry to any surplus reserves in its balance sheet;`
  line
  line `(c) the extent to which understatement or overstatement of any surplus of income over`
  line `expenditure or any shortfall of expenditure over income has been indicated in the auditors report and`
  line `the reasons for such understatement or overstatement;`
  line
  line `(d) the productivity of research projects undertaken by the Institute measured in accordance with`
  line `such norms as may be specified by any statutory regulatory authority;`
  line
  line `(e) appointments of the officers and teachers of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(f) benchmark and internal standards set by the Institute, including the nature of innovations in`
  line `teaching, research and application of knowledge.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director shall also be bound to give the complete information and explanations in its report`
  line `aforesaid on every reservation, qualification or adverse remark contained in the auditors' report.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (23242)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Annual report of each Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23242&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual report of each Institute shall be prepared under`
  line `the direction of the Board, which shall include, among other matters, the steps taken by the Institute`
  line `towards the fulfilment of its objects and an outcome based assessment of the research being undertaken in`
  line `such Institute, and be submitted to the Board on or before such date as may be specified and the Board`
  line `shall consider the report in its annual meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The annual report on its approval by the Board shall be published on the website of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(3) The annual report of each Institute shall be submitted to the Central Government who shall, as`
  line `soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (23243)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Council of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23243&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) In order that there may be better coordination between the Institutes,`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish, with effect from such date`
  line `as may be specified in the notification, there shall be established for all the Institutes specified in column`
  line `(5) of the Schedule, a central body to be called the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall consist of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the Minister of the Central Government in charge of technical education, who shall be the`
  line `Chairperson of the Council, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) two members of Parliament of India (one member to be nominated by Speaker of Lok Sabha`
  line `and one member to be nominated by Chairperson of Rajya Sabha), ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) Secretary, Government of India, Ministry of Human Resource Development, Department of`
  line `Higher Education;`
  line
  line `(iv) the Chairpersons of each of the Institutes, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) the Directors of each of the Institutes, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) the Director-General, Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vii) three persons to be nominated by the Central Government, one each to represent the Ministry`
  line `concerned with Finance, Science and Technology and Information Technology;`
  line
  line `(viii) three persons to be nominated by Visitor, who shall be persons having special knowledge or`
  line `practical experience in respect of industry, academia, engineering, alumni and social sciences to be`
  line `nominated by the Council from a panel comprised of two names recommended by each Institute;`
  line
  line `(ix) one representative of University Grants Commission;`
  line
  line `(x) one representative of All India Council of Technical Education; and`
  line
  line `(xi) Chairperson, Central Board of Secondary Education.`
  line
  line `(3) An officer of the Department of Higher Education, Government of India, concerned with technical`
  line `education shall be nominated by that Government to act as the Secretary of the Council.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council may, at its discretion, constitute a Standing Committee of the Indian Institute of`
  line `Information Technology Council to assist the Council in discharge of its duties and responsibilities.`
  line
  line `(5) The expenditure on the Council shall be met by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (23244)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Term of office and allowances payable to members of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2020, s. 2, for the word "elected" (w.e.f. 10-10-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23244&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this section, the term of office of a member of the Council, other than an ex officio member,`
  line `shall be for a period of three years from the date of nomination.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as he holds the office by virtue`
  line `of which he is a member.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of a member ^1[nominated] under clause (ii) of sub-section (2) of section 40`
  line `shall expire as soon as he ceases to be a member of the House which ^1[nominated] him.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, an outgoing member shall, unless the Council`
  line `directs, continue in office until another person is nominated as a member in his place.`
  line
  line `(5) Members of the Council shall be entitled to travelling and such other allowances, as may be`
  line `prescribed, for attending meetings of the Council or its Committees thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (23245)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Function and duties of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23245&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall work to coordinate the activities of all`
  line `the Institutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Council shall perform the following`
  line `functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to advise on matters relating to the duration of the courses, the degrees and other academic`
  line `distinctions to be conferred by the Institutes, admission standards and other academic matters;`
  line
  line `(b) to lay down policy regarding cadres, methods of recruitment and conditions of service of`
  line `employees, institution of scholarships and free-ships, levying of fees and other matters of common`
  line interest;
  line
  line `(c) to examine the development plans of each Institute and to approve such of them as are`
  line `considered necessary and also to indicate broadly the financial implications of such approved plans;`
  line
  line `(d) to examine the annual budget estimates of each Institute and to recommend to the Central`
  line `Government the allocation of funds for that purpose;`
  line
  line `(e) to recommend to the Central Government, the institution of scholarships including research`
  line `and for the benefit of students belonging to the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and Other`
  line `Backward Classes of citizens;`
  line
  line `(f) to recommend to the Central Government, proposals for establishment of new Institutes of`
  line `Information Technology;`
  line
  line `(g) to advise the Visitor, if so required, in respect of any function to be performed by him under`
  line `this Act; and`
  line
  line `(h) to perform such other functions as may be referred to it by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall derogate the powers and functions vested by law in the`
  line `Board or Senate or other authorities of each Institute.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson of the Council shall ordinarily preside at the meetings of the Council and in his`
  line `or her absence, any other member, chosen by the Members present from amongst themselves at the`
  line `meeting, shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall meet once in every year and follow such procedure in its meetings as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (23246)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23246&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may,`
  line `after previous publication, by notification, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the travelling and other allowances payable to members of the Council under sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 41;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed in the meetings of the Council under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 42.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (23247)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Acts and proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23247&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `No act of the Council, or any`
  line `Institute, Board or Senate or any other body set-up under this Act or the Statutes, shall be invalid merely`
  line `by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in or defect in the constitution thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case;`
  line
  line `(c) any defect in the selection, nomination or appointment of a person acting as a member thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (23248)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Returns and information to be provided to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23248&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Every Institute shall`
  line `furnish to the Central Government such returns or other information with respect to its policies or`
  line `activities as the Central Government may, for the purpose of reporting to Parliament or for the making of`
  line `policy, from time to time require.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (23249)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23249&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The Institute shall carry out such directions`
  line `as may be issued to it from time to time by the Central Government for the efficient administration of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (23250)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Institute to be public authority under Right to Information Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23250&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Right`
  line `to Information Act, 2005 (22 of 2005) shall apply to each Institute, defined in clause (h) of section 2 of`
  line `the Right to Information Act, 2005.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (23251)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23251&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act—`
  line
  line `(a) the Board of Governors of an Institute functioning as such immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall continue to so function until a new Board is constituted for that`
  line `Institute under this Act, but on the constitution of a new Board under this Act, the members of the`
  line `Board holding office before the commencement of this Act shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `(b) every Senate constituted in relation to every Institute before the commencement of this Act`
  line `shall be deemed to be the Senate constituted under this Act until a Senate is constituted under this Act`
  line `for the Institute, but on the constitution of the new Senate under this Act, the members of the Senate`
  line `holding office before the commencement of this Act shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `(c) the Statutes, Ordinances, rules, regulations and bye-laws of each existing Institute as in force,`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall continue to apply to the corresponding`
  line `institute in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act until the first Statutes and`
  line `the Ordinances are made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) any student who joined classes of the existing Institute on or after the academic year`
  line `2007-2008 or completed the course on or after the academic year 2010-2011 shall for the purpose of`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 7, be deemed to have pursued a course of study in the existing`
  line `Institute located at Kancheepuram only if such student has not already been awarded degree or`
  line `diploma for the same course of study.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), if it`
  line `considers necessary and expedient to do so, by notification, take such measures which may be necessary`
  line `for the transfer of the existing Institute mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule to the corresponding`
  line `Institute mentioned under column (5) of the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (23252)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23252&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act the Central Government, may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of the period of three years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be, after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (23253)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Laying of rules and notification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075&sectionId=23253&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00035_201430_1517807328075
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made and every notification issued by the Central`
  line `Government under this Act, shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or notification or both Houses agree that the rule or notification should not be made or issued,`
  line `the rule or notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the`
  line `case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule or notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
